---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
// Mocks + the site wordmark live in apps/landing as the single source of
// truth — the blog renders the same product visuals + identity as the
// homepage, so importing them here keeps the two surfaces from drifting
// on every UI tweak.
import DockBar from '../../../landing/src/components/DockBar.astro';
import CardMock from '../../../landing/src/components/CardMock.astro';
import AskMock from '../../../landing/src/components/AskMock.astro';
import Wordmark from '../../../landing/src/components/Wordmark.astro';
---

<Layout title="Slashtalk — we built a presence dock for our team. Here's why.">
	<div class="min-h-screen bg-white text-neutral-900">
		<header
			class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl items-center justify-between px-6 py-6"
		>
			<Wordmark />
			<nav class="flex items-center gap-2 sm:gap-7">
				<a
					href="/blog"
					class="hidden text-sm font-medium text-neutral-600 transition hover:text-neutral-900 sm:inline"
					>Blog</a
				>
				<a
					href="https://github.com/HereNotThere/slashtalk"
					class="hidden text-sm font-medium text-neutral-600 transition hover:text-neutral-900 sm:inline"
					>GitHub</a
				>
				<button
					type="button"
					data-download
					class="rounded-full bg-neutral-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white transition hover:bg-neutral-700"
				>
					Download
				</button>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-8 pb-16 sm:pt-12 sm:pb-24">
			<article class="space-y-7 text-[17px] leading-[1.7] text-neutral-700">
				<h1
					class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 sm:text-4xl"
				>
					We built a presence dock for our team. Here's why.
				</h1>

				<p>
					Something has changed about software teams in the last eighteen
					months, and we don't think anyone has named it yet.
				</p>

				<p>
					Every engineer on a small team can now ship production quality
					work, <em class="italic text-neutral-900">fast</em>. The output
					per engineer has multiplied by magnitudes.
				</p>

				<p>
					The part that gets less attention: coordination got harder by
					exactly the same multiple.
				</p>

				<p>
					If one person ships ten times more code, in ten times more
					places, branching off in ten times more directions — then the
					cost of knowing what your teammates are doing scales with it.
					The standup that used to fit a day into two sentences now can't
					fit an hour. The ticket board that tracked who-owns-what now
					lags reality by days. The Slack channel meant to keep everyone
					in the loop becomes the thing you mute to get anything done.
				</p>

				<p>
					This isn't a tooling preference. It's a structural mismatch.
					The coordination layer was built for a pace of work that no
					longer exists.
				</p>

				<p>
					The same tools that let us ship this fast also force us, for
					the first time, to <strong
						class="font-semibold text-neutral-900"
						>write down what we're trying to do.</strong
					> Every prompt is a small, live, machine-readable description
					of the work — composed by the person doing the work, at the
					moment they're doing it.
				</p>

				<p>
					That has never been true before. The whole history of project
					management has been a workaround for not having it - standups,
					tickets, status threads.
				</p>

				<p>
					Now it does - the signal for work is sitting right there in
					the prompts, generated as a byproduct of the work itself.
				</p>

				<p>The opportunity is to read it.</p>

				<hr class="my-12 border-neutral-200" />

				<p>So that's what we're building.</p>

				<p>
					<strong class="font-semibold text-neutral-900"
						>Slashtalk is a presence dock for small teams shipping at
						this new pace.</strong
					> It sits on top of your desktop. Each teammate is a card.
					Each card shows what they're shipping right now — recent PRs,
					active sessions, the work in flight — synthesized from their
					prompts and their PRs.
				</p>

				<figure class="my-10 flex justify-center">
					<DockBar />
				</figure>

				<figure class="my-10 flex justify-center">
					<CardMock />
				</figure>

				<p>
					When someone wants to know what features the team is working
					on today, they ask the dock instead of pinging engineers.
					When two people are about to collide on the same file, it's
					flagged. The answers come from the work itself.
				</p>

				<figure class="my-10">
					<AskMock />
				</figure>

				<p>
					We built it for ourselves, because we're a small remote team
					that ran headfirst into the problem we just described. We're
					now shipping more with fewer interruptions and bonus - its
					fun to feel like your team is hanging out with you while you
					work.
				</p>

				<p>
					If you're on a team where the shipping got faster but the
					coordination got worse — try Slashtalk and tell us what you
					think.
				</p>

				<div id="install" class="scroll-mt-8 pt-4">
					<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row">
						<button
							type="button"
							data-download
							class="inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 rounded-full bg-neutral-900 px-7 py-3.5 text-base font-medium text-white shadow-sm transition hover:bg-neutral-700"
						>
							<svg
								viewBox="0 0 24 24"
								fill="currentColor"
								width="18"
								height="18"
								aria-hidden="true"
							>
								<path
									d="M16.365 1.43c0 1.14-.46 2.235-1.21 3.034-.808.86-2.121 1.527-3.207 1.443-.142-1.078.452-2.21 1.18-2.92.815-.79 2.21-1.398 3.237-1.557zm3.926 17.14c-.612 1.345-.905 1.946-1.694 3.137-1.103 1.661-2.66 3.731-4.59 3.748-1.715.016-2.156-1.122-4.485-1.107-2.328.014-2.812 1.13-4.527 1.114-1.93-.018-3.404-1.882-4.508-3.543-3.085-4.65-3.41-10.106-1.506-13.005 1.353-2.06 3.488-3.265 5.495-3.265 2.043 0 3.328 1.122 5.022 1.122 1.643 0 2.643-1.124 5.014-1.124 1.789 0 3.685.974 5.034 2.66-4.426 2.42-3.703 8.747.745 10.263z"
								></path>
							</svg>
							Download for macOS
						</button>
						<span class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
							Free · macOS 13+ · Apple Silicon &amp; Intel
						</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>

		<footer
			class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col items-center justify-between gap-4 border-t border-neutral-200 px-6 py-8 text-sm text-neutral-500 sm:flex-row"
		>
			<div>
				Slashtalk — from <a
					href="https://x.com/TownsLabs"
					class="text-neutral-700 underline decoration-neutral-300 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-neutral-700"
					>Towns Labs</a
				>
			</div>
			<div class="flex items-center gap-6">
				<a href="/blog" class="transition hover:text-neutral-900"
					>Blog</a
				>
				<a
					href="https://github.com/HereNotThere/slashtalk"
					class="transition hover:text-neutral-900">GitHub</a
				>
				<a
					href="https://x.com/TownsLabs"
					class="transition hover:text-neutral-900">Twitter</a
				>
			</div>
		</footer>
	</div>
</Layout>

<script>
	document
		.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-download]')
		.forEach((button) => {
			button.addEventListener('click', () => {
				console.log('[slashtalk] Download for macOS clicked');
			});
		});
</script>
